snippet.textDisplay: Ollie has been converted to the Loader tractor and you will too🤣🤣🤣 Martin Walsh is great to deal with and Major make one of the best tanks on the market. If you are thinking of the dribble bar or trailing shoe, you should buy new. The specialised tanks have reinforcement and attachment points for the trailing shoe/dribble bar. I bought a Major 2300 with trailing shoe and I'm delighted with it. Because of the application via trailing shoe, I can reduce chemical fertilizer use due to better utilisation of slurry,  grass growth will be better. Are there any grants available for Uk farmers to transition to this type of application?
